messages.message: When using the native Excel feature the following Excel files do not ingest into Build properly:
These are confidential files not to be used outside the purpose to diagnose the issues with Native Excel processing

@Dale DeLoy We are aware of some of the limitations with rendering rich objects, text that span across rows and columns.

@Aayush can you please help to list the limitations here?

Get the following error:
*Failed to add all documents*No project documents were created successfully. Failures: [AddFileFailure(reason='failing to read ibocr object: Error when reading the filename (full path is sixfold/IB-Testing/fs/Instabase Drive/aihub/019132da-cb6c-7aa8-9aa9-a735b09c5584/documents/out/ee92a27e-861b-401c-b113-79395e986778__21091302_Statement of Values_60942D8E-0000-CA61-8ABD-8DAF4159E789.XLSX.ibdoc): Cannot open a non-existent file in rb mode. Path: sixfold/IB-Testing/fs/Instabase Drive/aihub/019132da-cb6c-7aa8-9aa9-a735b09c5584

Hey Dale, yes the rich rendering and formatting and other advanced features is a limitation currently. We have it listed out in this doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ocA9fP0HN01mQvcR5RPEG0I0fGnzQ8kOyRAQZQxZKjw/edit#heading=h.4c41dk40ht5r
Is that the issue with these docs?
~I am able to upload and digitise the docs with build project in Prod. Can you retry with a new project?~
@Aayush can you check on the logs?
Same issue/error with a new project.  Be sure to have Tables and Native Excel checked
@Dale DeLoy I found the root cause for this issue. As a workaround, can you rename the file extensions from XLSX to xlsx.
